text: Maayan Furman-Shahaf (; born November 9, 1986) is an Israeli high jumper and triple jumper. She holds a personal best of for the high jump and for the triple jump. She competed for Israel at the 2013 World Championships in Athletics in the women's high jump, coming in fifth at 1.88 m. She represented her country at the European Athletics Championships in 2012 and 2016. ==National titles== *Israeli Athletics Championships **High jump: 2007, 2009, 2012, 2013, 2014, 2015, 2016 == References == Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Israeli female high jumpers Category:Israeli female triple jumpers Category:World Athletics Championships athletes for Israel
